</div>You still don&#8217;t get my argument.  <br />
<br />
I don&#8217;t have a problem with someone risking for their principles, I have a problem with someone risking their lives and orphaning a child over a <i>stupid</i> principle.  A firefighter risks his life in order to save lives.  Not only is this noble, it&#8217;s his job.<br />
<br />
This woman risked her life because JW&#8217;s have a questionable interpretation of ambiguous biblical text.  Those are not two similar principles.  For the principle argument to work, in order to compare Firefighting to Blood Transfusions, you need to keep it abstract.  I want to look more closely at the principles in question.  Not all principles are noble, some are just plain stupid.  Risking in order to save others is not the same as risking because the Bible told you so.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		
